    <p class="lead">Sooner of later you will be faced with unfamiliar letter forms. Or a few letters and numbers may be so hard to decipher that you are not at all sure what you are looking at. This page offers some help on viewing the images, on understanding the hand-writing found in old registers and on how to enter information that you cannot be sure about. </p>
    <p>As you gain experience as a transcriber, you will find it easier to recognise letters, digits and even words. You will also find a dedicated image viewer useful. For those parts of a register entry where you remain unsure, use our Uncertain Character Format: this enables you to enter as much information as possible, in a way that is compatible with a database search.</p>
