    <p>The terminal ‘s’ tends to fall between the two forms. See fig. 4–6.</p>
    <p>Also look at the capital ‘H’ in fig. 6</p>
    <p>Within a word the double-s is written with a long ‘s’ followed by a short ‘s’; looking like an fs.</p>
